    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** serving as our primary offensive engines. **Gunnar Henderson** leads the squad with a 79.41 efficiency score, bolstered by a massive +16% park factor and the optimal leadoff spot, making him a must-start despite the absence of an opposing starter projection. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** follows closely at 71.02; while he faces a slight dynamic platoon disadvantage against the right-handed Bailey Ober, his elite 0.384 xwOBA and a +12% bump due to Ober's higher xERA (4.51) solidify his position as a cornerstone anchor. **Jacob Wilson** also provides significant value (69.82), as his profile benefits immensely from a favorable park factor and a manageable matchup against the left-handed Noah Cameron.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Brady House**, who posted a respectable 49.53 score against Freddy Peralta. While **Brady House** offered a +2% boost for his stolen base potential against Peralta\u2019s slow delivery, the optimizer opted for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.56) instead. The deciding factor was **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**'s +14% platoon edge against the righty, which effectively neutralized the SP skill deficit and kept our 2B slot productive. Meanwhile, we remain cautious with **Luis Robert Jr.** (58.57) and **Marcell Ozuna** (59.84); while both are cleared to start, their scores are dampened by dynamic platoon hurdles and unfavorable park factors. Owners should monitor the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Drake Baldwin**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** throughout the afternoon, as any drop in their projected batting order could trigger a swift re-evaluation of their efficiency scores.",
